RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1 1/16M Turf CR: 82. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since January 15 Allowed 2 lbs. (One win for $25,000 or less will not be considered when determining eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: A CROWN FOR KITTEN saved ground in the early stages while unhurried, maintained position through the backstretch run, was roused four wide into the stretch, came within aim at the furlong grounds, responded to steady urging in deep stretch, drew to even terms with FINNLEY'S KITTEN inside of the sixteenth-marker and surged in the final strides to prevail. FINNLEY'S KITTEN tracked the moderate early fractions, was roused three wide along the far turn, advanced nearing mid-stretch, match strides with A CROWN FOR KITTEN to the sixteenth-marker, took a narrow lead on that rival in deep stretch, battled gamely to the finish and was bested on the wire for the win, while clear of the rest for second. TURIAF broke alertly and dictated terms early on, ceded the lead to AMANDA ROSE heading into the backstretch run and stalked that rival to the second turn, confronted AMANDA ROSE nearing the furlong marker, took command into the final furlong, was not able to match strides with the top two in deep stretch and held on for third. AMANDA ROSE was close up in the early running, prompted the pace along the first turn then assumed command into the backstretch run, set decent fractions into the second turn, held the lead to mid-stretch, could not keep pace with oncoming rivals in the late stages and weakened. COUNCILWOMAN JILLY lunged at the start and was away slowly, was allowed to settle through the backstretch run, saved ground into the second turn and offered a mild late rally in the stretch. NOT NOW I'M BIZZIE was allowed to settle, was never far back while saving ground into the far turn, raced two wide into the stretch and lacked a late rally.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS BELLIMBUSTO was allowed to settle in the early running, was roused four wide approaching the quarter marker, loomed at mid-stretch, closed determinedly in the late stages, came within aim of JUST A LITTLE LUCK inside of the sixteenth-marker and kept to task in the final strides to win the nod at the finish. JUST A LITTLE LUCK raced close to the solid early pace, pressed BLACK ZABAT to the quarter marker, battled with that rival in upper stretch then took a narrow lead at the furlong grounds, was kept to steady urging while leading to deep stretch, felt pressure from MISS BELLIMBUSTO inside of the sixteenth-marker and was nailed on the wire for the win, while holding for second. EM N HOLL'S FIESTA tracked the decent early pace, advanced three wide on the turn, chased the leaders while within aim at mid-stretch, closed well late, could not reel in the top pair in deep stretch and was clear at the finish for third. ELECTRIC LETTUCE tracked the decent early pace, saved ground along the turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch and lacked a response in the final stages. HOW ABOUT A FRESCA was unhurried in the early going, saved ground to the quarter marker, trailed to the furlong grounds and offered a mild late bid. BLACK ZABAT broke alertly and showed good early speed, was pressed to the quarter marker while slowing down the fractions, was set down in upper stretch and battled for the lead to the furlong pole, could not keep pace in deep stretch and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWILIGHT EMPIRE was unhurried in the early going, trailed along the backstretch run, improved position three wide on the second turn, slipped to the two path nearing the top of the lane, loomed at mid-stretch, matched strides with PERSUASIVE LIPS inside of the furlong marker, took command from the tiring pacesetter inside of the sixteenth-marker and held the runner-up at bay in the final strides to prevail. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY SUNSHINE tracked the early pace from the second flight, raced outside of rivals while well positioned through the backstretch run, gained ground three wide on the far turn, slipped to the two path in upper stretch, confronted TIZONA and battled with that foe to the furlong grounds, responded to urging inside of the furlong marker and took a narrow lead heading to deep stretch, kept to task in the final stages and held in a drive over the stubborn runner-up. TIZONA was hustled leaving the break and dictated terms in the early going, was well rated through modest fractions to the half-mile marker, held foes at bay to the quarter pole, was confronted by MY SUNSHINE in upper stretch, met that bid and held a narrow lead to mid-stretch, stubbornly battled against MY SUNSHINE inside of the furlong marker and was outfinished in deep stretch, while holding safely for second. ON RAGLAN ROAD was forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the modest fractions from a rail position through the backstretch run, saved ground to the quarter marker, tipped three wide in upper stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker, offered a mild late bid but could not reel in the top two in deep stretch and held safely for third. RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 6F All Weather Track CR: 92. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 15 Allowed 2 lbs. (One win for $25,000 or less will not be considered when determining eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CANDY'S CLONE broke well, got in good position down the backstretch, tracked the leading pair to the turn, began a bid with three furlongs to run, awaited room turning for home, split horses at the top of the stretch, shifted in to avoid contact with SHE'S SO SHINY then straightened out and ran away from the field. TAMARA MINE broke outward when bothered by SHE'S SO SHINY after the break which in turn forced the two horses to the outside to break outward as well, settled on the outside of the tracking trio to the turn, responded when asked to pick it up near the five-sixteenths pole, was five wide as the field fanned out turning for home, then ran on well down the middle of the track to gain the place while no match for the winner. OLIVIA'S CHOICE (IRE) allowed to settle near the rear of the field in the early going, began a sustained rally from the half-mile marker, kept to the inside through the turn, tipped out for room in deep stretch and finished up well. MISS IVES broke outward at the break then raced between horses tracking the pacesetter down the backstretch, moved forward through the turn, had a difficult time finding running room in the stretch but ran some when clear in deep stretch. RESERVOIR was last away and trailed early, struggled to keep up through the turn despite the best efforts of the rider, stayed near the rail through the turn then mustered a mild rally in the stretch but was much too late. TOO BOSSY hustled from the break, established the lead with several in close pursuit, held to the three-sixteenths pole with three challengers to the outside then battled on gamely to the furlong marker but tired and stopped. SHE'S SO SHINY broke out, straightened, rushed up and settled just behind the lone pacesetter, moved up to challenge for the lead near the quarter pole, loomed a threat at the head of the stretch but weakened between horses and was unable to keep up in the late stages.
